
                                            Former Australia all-rounder, Shane Watson, was on hand to help Cena with his batting during a Sydney Thunder training session on Tuesday. 

                                         JOHANNESBURG - WWE superstar John Cena tried his hand at cricket during Big Bash League Franchise Sydney Thunder's training session in Australia on Tuesday.  Cena is in Australia promoting his new movie titled Ferdinand and thought it would be a great idea to improve his cricket skills.  Former Australia all-rounder, Shane Watson, was on hand to help Cena with his batting during a Sydney Thunder training session on Tuesday.  Watson and Cena shared the experience on their Twitter pages.  The Big Bash League kicks off on 9 December with the Melbourne Renegades taking on the Sydney Thunder and concludes with the final on 4 February. 